Package searcher

Searchers are objects that aim to solve the "find kth element" problem from the lecture. A Searcher is given both the array that it is to search in, and the index, k, specifying the kth largest entry that it is to find, when it is constructed.
Version:
September 2019
Author:
Hugh Osborne
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CleverSearcher
    Implements the Searcher class to find the kth largest element in a randomly generated array by creating a testing array of k elements that parses over the main array, comparing elements.
    CleverSearcherTest  
    CleverSearcherTimer  
    FullCleverSearcher  
    FullCleverSearcherTest  
    FullCleverSearcherTimer  
    Searcher
    A class that owns an int array, and an index.
    SearcherTest  
    SimpleSearcher
    Implements the find (kth) element method by sorting and indexing, using the naive method of first sorting the whole array and then accessing the (array.length-k)th element.
    SimpleSearcherTest  
    SimpleSearcherTimer
    A timer implementation for simple searchers that times the findElement method
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IndexingError
    Use to report index out of bounds errors
